cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.NI 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it deals with predicting missing links in complex networks. It could also belong to cs.SD (Software Development and Programming) as it presents a practical approach for link prediction. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a new framework for link prediction. It may also fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as it discusses the computing complexity of the proposed approach. Finally, it could be classified under cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as it deals with network topology and information theory.
